The National Taxi Alliance (NTA) has on Monday said it will transport mourners for free to the main memorial service of the struggle icon Winnie Madikizela-Mandela at the Orlando Stadium on Thursday. National Spokesperson Theo Malele said this is the least contribution they can do to show their appreciation to Mam’ Winnie for fighting for the country’s freedom. “The taxis will ferry mourners from all the five regions of the Gauteng province at no costs to the African National Congress, Government and the mourners. “As direct beneficiaries of the liberation struggle waged by gallant and selfless fighters like our beloved departed mother of the nation this is the least contribution we can make to show our appreciation of the suffering and toiled she and others went through for us to enjoy the freedom we have today,” said Malele. -TNA Reporter 